{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Impose a 50p surcharge on clothes hangers",
        "additional_details": "Millions of clothes hangers are used each year in the UK, and far too many of these are simply thrown away, rather than being reused or recycled. \r\n \r\nImposing a surcharge for clothes hangers would help raise awareness of the environmental impact of clothes hangers, and help fund initiatives to enable reuse/recycling or tackle environmental impacts.",
        "background": "The Government should ban clothes hangers being given away free with clothes, and require retailers to add a 50p per clothes hanger surcharge.",
